# Local MCP dev audit

This rule lives in **`.cursor/rules/local/`** (gitignored directory). Cursor loads all `.mdc` files under `.cursor/rules/`, including subfolders. You can rename this file; the whole `local/` directory stays out of git.

When working on `agent-brain` MCP, hooks, or install code:

1. Call `route_task` at turn start.
2. Before finishing, run: `python3 docs/superpowers/mcp-audit/audit.py`
3. Read `docs/superpowers/MCP-INTEGRATION-AUDIT.md` for new issues; fix in the same session.
4. Re-run audit until clean or only manual steps remain (restart Cursor).
5. **Never commit** `docs/superpowers/` or anything under `.cursor/rules/local/`.
6. **Local-only ops docs** (GTM playbooks, launch metrics, video shot lists, draft posts) belong under `docs/superpowers/gtm/` — not `docs/gtm/` or public `docs/`.

Auto-fix is on by default (`audit.py` syncs hooks and runs `install --global`).
